Text.SourceString: So the rumors were true after all. Welcome to town!//<portrait=doubt>We got a new scientist in town last month too. Can’t remember his name, though.//<portrait=normal>Anyway, I hope you like it here.
Sure, sure, it’s nice to meet you too! My name is <NPCName>Emma</>.
I get my ingredients from <NPCName>Sam</>.//I also scavenge around the island for them.
<NPCName>Dippa</> is the one decorating my truck. I don’t have an eye for all this artsy stuff.//<portrait=happy>It’s something else, isn’t it?
The kids love ’em.
I get my ingredients from <NPCName>Sam</>.//I also use some vegetables that I grow in my garden.
<NPCName>Sam</> has a variety of items for sale. His place is one-stop shopping for the food truck.
<NPCName>Sam</> has a variety of items for sale. His place is one-stop shopping for the food truck.
I go out of town sometimes. Not often, though, and usually only on weekends.
School ends around 4 pm.//That’s usually my prime selling time.
I go out of town sometimes.//<portrait=normal>Not often, though, and usually only on weekends.

School ends around 4 pm.//That’s usually my prime selling time.
Usually… Not always, though.//Sometimes I’m lucky to sell five packs.
Grapes and rice can be fermented into alcoholic beverages in kegs. Did you know that?
Hmm… I can’t remember who told me.//<portrait=normal>Why? Does it matter?
It’s kind of nice to spend the weekend here.
My truck is closed today.//Probably wouldn’t get many customers, anyway.
It’s kind of nice to spend the weekend here.
I can’t believe it’s Sunday already. I’m still so tired from yesterday.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I can sneak in some beach time next weekend and lie out in the sun.
I don’t usually have any food left at the end of the day, because I don’t make a lot to begin with.
But when I do have leftovers, I refrigerate them to eat later.

But when I do have leftovers, I refrigerate them to eat later.
I don’t know why <NPCName>Dippa</> doesn’t just buy and sell art, you know?//<portrait=normal>They have an eye for it.
Me? Buying art? No, no. I don’t have what it takes…and I also don’t want to.//<portrait=happy>I like to keep moving all day.
Fishensips is just too loud for me.//<portrait=annoyed>The music hurts my ears, honestly.
Oh sure, sure. I think a lot of people like that… The loud music and sweaty crowds.//<portrait=happy>It’s just not my type of place.
I do my errands around Starlet Town on Wednesday or Thursday.//That way I can leave town on the weekend, if I need to.
Everything I sell is made fresh every day, by the way.//So you can be sure that you won’t be eating day-old meals.
I’m proud of that.
I don’t really like hanging out at Fishensips.//<portrait=normal>It’s too loud there.
I prefer the lake or just staying home… I hope you don’t think I’m dull!
Fishensips is just too loud for me.//<portrait=annoyed>The music hurts my ears, honestly.
Oh sure, sure. I think a lot of people like that… The loud music and sweaty crowds.//<portrait=happy>It’s just not my type of place.
Hmm… I seem to always run out of things.//Do I need to make a trip to Sam’s already?
Did you know that the creek in front of the mayor’s house was once dried up?//Oh, but it was so long ago… I doubt many people know about it.
It was all so sudden when we had that earthquake.//<portrait=happy>Then, bam! The creek was flowing again the next day.
Work, work, work… Eh, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I need to make a list before I go to the store, or else I buy too much.//<portrait=annoyed>So annoying!
I’ve been trying to cook something new to sell, like cookies or something.//But it’s easier said than done.
For some reason the kids don’t buy as much when I make anything else besides tacos.//<portrait=normal>Why is that, do you think?

I’ve been trying to cook something new to sell, like cookies or pizza.//But it’s easier said than done.
For some reason the kids don’t buy as much when I make anything else besides tacos.//<portrait=normal>Why is that, do you think?
Did you know that the creek in front of the mayor’s house was once dried up? Oh, but it was so long ago… I doubt many people know about it.
It was all so sudden when we had that earthquake. Then, bam! The creek was flowing again the next day.

Oh, you look confused.//Looking for something, <PlayerName>$player</>?
<NPCName>Erika</>? Hmm… I see her at school sometimes, but I don’t know where she might be today.
Oh, you look confused.//Looking for something, <PlayerName>$player</>?
<NPCName>Erika</>? Hmm… I see her at school sometimes, but I don’t know where she might be today.
I taught the kids a few tricks to make tacos. *laughs* I hope their parents don’t mind.
They seemed to pick it up quickly, I have to say. I wonder if the kids already learned that somewhere else.
I see <NPCName>Betty</> at school often. I think she’s teaching the kids every week.//<portrait=happy>But I’m not 100 percent certain.
<NPCName>Archie</> told me that he learned about coral reefs and the island’s ecosystem from <NPCName>Betty</>.//I guess she probably knows this place better than anyone.
I see <NPCName>Betty</> at school often. I think she’s teaching the kids every week.//<portrait=happy>But I’m not 100 percent certain.
<NPCName>Archie</> told me that he learned about coral reefs and the island’s ecosystem from <NPCName>Betty</>.//I guess she probably knows this place better than anyone.
I taught the kids at school a few tricks to make tacos. *laughs* I hope their parents don’t mind.
They seemed to pick it up quickly, I have to say.//I wonder if the kids already learned that somewhere else.
You can find all kinds of things around my house… Oh, like food, I mean!//<portrait=happy>There are wild mushrooms… Even fresh fruit sometimes.
If you find any wild fruit, feel free to take it, by the way.
I think I’m going to bring some tortillas to the Cherry Blossom Festival.//Do you think that’s tacky?
It’s always nice to gather with folks.
We’re halfway through Spring already and I haven’t done my house cleaning yet!
Everything is a mess! I can’t even find my old grill.
Oh! It’s the last week of Spring already! I really need to find my old grill.
You see, this is why we shouldn’t put things away.//Then people can’t see them, and people get irritated when they can’t find what they’re looking for.
Yes. I am, in fact, one of these people.
My birthday is on the thirteenth, and do you know who else has a birthday on the thirteenth?
<NPCName>Eva</>! We’ve made it a tradition to exchange gifts every year. It’s a little inside joke. Ha!
Going to the beach a lot, <PlayerName>$player</>?
We get a lot of bugs here over the Summer.//But there must be plenty over at the farm too, huh?//<portrait=doubt>I mean, the forest is right there.
But we also get a lot of cosmos… The flowers.//<portrait=normal>So I don’t want to complain too much about Summer.
I’m out of fish, so I guess I’m only selling vegan tacos tomorrow.
No, not a good time. I’ll go shopping for fish next week.//The vegetables will do for now.
Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> has been busy walking back and forth to town, lately.//I’m guessing he’s trying to get the Mooncake Festival ready.
It’s a lot of work being a mayor, you know.//Over the Summer I rarely caught him fishing at all, and he loves fishing.
So lovely to see the Fall decorations in town.//They always do an excellent job.
The whole town looks like a scene from a television show.
I remember the first Winter I opened my truck.//Almost the whole town showed up to celebrate with me.
No, it wasn’t a gathering or anything like that.//<portrait=happy>They came to help out and probably wanted to boost my business.
I have to scavenge extra hard during Winter because there’s not much around to begin with.
The temperature is just too cold. Plants can’t survive in the snow.
With less wild produce around for me to cook with, I have to be very…creative when it comes to my taco recipe.
I’ve been using a lot of substitutes lately.//<portrait=normal>I wonder if my customers even notice?
Isn’t there a saying that snow brings good luck?
Oh, is it the rain? Hmm… Maybe it is the rain.
<NPCName>Bree</>’s holding a yearly appreciation dinner for the mayor, where we’ll get to exchange gifts.
It’s great, I suppose. It’s very nice of her to do that.//But it’s hard to find a good gift… I’m just not a great gift giver.
I don’t travel during the Winter. I’m afraid the truck might get stuck in the middle of a snowstorm.
I can’t remember the last time I changed the tires, to be perfectly honest. It’s worrisome if you ask me.
Please watch your boots. I’d hate to mop my floor again.
Wah, the rain is that bad, huh?
I don’t like going out in the rain, so I usually just spend my day cooking.
With this rain, though, tomorrow there may be more wild fruit than usual around the island.
Wishful thinking on my part.
I need to crank up the heater in here.
Please watch your boots. I’d hate to mop my floor again.
Wah, the storm is that bad, huh?
I don’t like going out in the rain, so I usually just spend my day cooking.
The storm may bring out more wild vegetables around the island.//I don’t know for sure, but it’s worth checking!
I’ll do it tomorrow. Fingers crossed.
I need to crank up the heater in here.
It feels like it was just snowing yesterday, and now it’s snowing again today.
What luck, eh?
Isn’t there a saying that snow brings good luck?
Oh, is it the rain? Hmm… Maybe it is the rain.
What a great day to be outside.
I think I may take a quick walk later, before heading home.//You know, to enjoy the weather.
You need a really good skillet to make tacos.
You can use any kind of fish to make fish tacos.//<portrait=happy>Honestly, after I cook the fish, I can’t even taste the difference. It’s all in the seasoning.
It’s easier than you think to make good vegan tacos.//I personally like to use bell peppers, but you can use any Summer or Fall vegetables you want.
When there are no customers I try to nap, and right now you’re kind of in the way.
No offense.
I have no idea where this creek is flowing from… But I’m not one to explore nature, so I can never bring myself to find out.
Heading down to town, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Please watch yourself. Try not to step on anything, okay?
I’m glad you came to visit.
It’s easier than you think to make good vegan tacos.//I personally like to use bell peppers, but you can use any Summer or Fall vegetables you want.
Just had the time to do meal prep.//Ah, my hands are so dirty.
Might as well marinate some chard for burritos.
*furiously chopping vegetables*
I put in some red cabbage, when it’s in season.//<portrait=happy>It has that nice crunchy texture.
It’s good to see you in such good spirits, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Hmm… What else do I need?
I just buy my tortillas here. It takes too much time to make them from scratch.
Knowing where this fruit is grown helps me feel more connected to the island.//It also supports local farmers, right?
I might open my truck later.//<portrait=doubt>I don’t know yet.
It’s easier than you think to make good vegan tacos.//I personally like to use bell peppers, but you can use any Summer or Fall vegetables you want.
I put in some red cabbage, when it’s in season.//<portrait=happy>It has that nice crunchy texture.
Hmm… I may need to buy extra dyes today.
Ah, I should’ve packed an extra lunch.//<portrait=doubt>I ate mine too early, and I can feel my stomach growling again.
Are you on a picnic too?
